    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1926-04-12T11:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1926-04-12T11:00:00-05:00" n="218"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d218">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">838.00/2224: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The High Commissioner in Haiti</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Russell</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Port au Prince</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1926-04-12T11:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 12, 1926—11 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received April 14—8:15 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>37. President Borno reelected President for 4 years by National Assembly this
                    morning by a majority vote of 19 out of 20 present, other vote was a blank.
                    Session was held before the public, including the diplomatic corps, press and
                    many of the candidates.</p>
                <pb facs="0493" n="397" xml:id="pg_397"/>
                <p>Immediately called on President Borno and congratulated him on his reelection.
                    President Borno stated that he had decided to run for reelection for the sake of
                    continuing [omission?] and that he was prepared to take all risks, even that of
                    assassination.</p>
                <p>Some excitement in the city among the opposition but do not anticipate any
                    serious trouble as the <hi rend="italic">gendarmerie</hi> is prepared to handle
                    any that should arise.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Russell</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
